# Development Setup

## Prerequisites

- Node.js 18+ or Bun 1.0+
- Git
- Python 3.10+ (for docs)
{{#if useDocker}}
- Docker & Docker Compose
{{/if}}

## Getting Started

### 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/{{author}}/{{name}}.git
cd {{name}}
```

### 2. Install Dependencies

```bash
{{#if useBun}}
bun install
{{else}}
npm install
{{/if}}
```

### 3. Set Up Environment

```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your values
```

### 4. Start Development Server

```bash
{{#if useBun}}
bun run dev
{{else}}
npm run dev
{{/if}}
```

## Code Quality

### Linting

```bash
# Check for issues
{{#if useBun}}
bun run lint
{{else}}
npm run lint
{{/if}}

# Auto-fix issues
{{#if useBun}}
bun run lint:fix
{{else}}
npm run lint:fix
{{/if}}
```

### Formatting

```bash
{{#if useBun}}
bun run format
{{else}}
npm run format
{{/if}}
```

### Type Checking

```bash
{{#if useBun}}
bun run typecheck
{{else}}
npm run typecheck
{{/if}}
```

## Testing

```bash
# Run all tests
{{#if useBun}}
bun test
{{else}}
npm test
{{/if}}

# Run with coverage
{{#if useBun}}
bun test --coverage
{{else}}
npm run test:coverage
{{/if}}
```

## Documentation

### Build Docs

```bash
# Install Python dependencies
pip install -r requirements-docs.txt

# Serve locally
mkdocs serve

# Build for production
mkdocs build
```

### API Documentation

API documentation is auto-generated from source code comments.

```bash
{{#if useBun}}
bun run docs:backend
{{else}}
npm run docs:backend
{{/if}}
```

## Project Structure

```
{{name}}/
├── .arbiter/          # Arbiter spec files
├── backend/           # Backend service
├── frontend/          # Frontend app
├── docs/              # Documentation
├── scripts/           # Build scripts
└── tests/             # Integration tests
```

## IDE Setup

### VS Code

Recommended extensions:

- Biome (for JS/TS)
- Tailwind CSS IntelliSense
- TypeScript Vue Plugin (if using Vue)

### Settings

Add to `.vscode/settings.json`:

```json
{
  "editor.defaultFormatter": "biomejs.biome",
  "editor.formatOnSave": true
}
```
